==Korean==

===Etymology===
From ''seol'' [[설]] ([[snow]]) + ''nong'' [[렁]] (thick, strong, concentrated) + tang [[탕]] ([[soup]])

===Pronunciation===
*The 2000 South Korean Revised: seol nong tang
*McCune-Reischauer: sol nong t'ang
*Yale: sel nong thang

===Noun===
[[설렁탕]] ('''[[雪]][[濃]][[湯]]''')

# a soup made from [[ox]] or [[beef]] bones, meat, and other seasonings